Explanation:
- `MATCH(A2, Data!$F$4:$N$4, 0)` finds the position of the year within the year row (range F‑N).  
- `OFFSET(Data!$F$4, 10, …)` starts at the year cell (row 4, column F), moves down 10 rows to row 14, and then moves right by the MATCH result to land on the value column (G, K, O …).  
- `IFERROR(..., "")` returns an empty string when the year isn’t found.

